SECTION 3: 120-CELL TOPOLOGY
----------------------------------------------------------------------

The 120-cell (regular 4D polytope, H4 symmetry group, order 14400):

Combinatorial data:
  3-cells (dodecahedra): 120
  2-faces (pentagons):   720
  1-edges:               1200
  0-vertices:            600
  Euler characteristic:  120 - 720 + 1200 - 600 = 0

The Euler characteristic of any convex 4-polytope is 0. CHECK: PASS

3D boundary structure:
  The 120-cell lives in S^3 (3-sphere) as its vertex set.
  Symmetry group: H4 (binary icosahedral extension), order 14400.

The Poincare Homology Sphere (PHS):
  Construction: take a solid dodecahedron; identify opposite faces
  with a 36-degree clockwise twist. The result is a closed 3-manifold.
  pi_1(PHS) = binary icosahedral group I* = <r,s | r^5=s^3=(rs)^2>
  Order: |I*| = 120
  H_1(PHS) = abelianisation(I*) = 0  (I* is a perfect group)
  H_2(PHS) = 0,  H_3(PHS) = Z

Audit of 'lens space L(5,1)' claim in supervisor notes:
  L(5,1) has pi_1 = Z/5Z,  H_1 = Z/5Z.
  The dodecahedron/120-cell gives PHS with pi_1 = I* (order 120), H_1 = 0.
  These are DIFFERENT 3-manifolds.
  CORRECTED CLAIM: The 3D cross-section of the 120-cell cavity
  has Poincare Homology Sphere topology, NOT L(5,1).
  The wormhole signature is the H4 eigenmode (D4/D2=2.5), not L(5,1) surgery.

  |I*| = 2 * |A5| = 2 * 60 = 120
  A5 is simple and non-abelian => I* is perfect => H_1(PHS) = 0. CONFIRMED.

